1)How do you structure Angular projects in real-time applications?
We follow a feature-based architecture with core, shared, and feature modules to improve scalability and maintainability.

2)Why do we create models in Angular?
Models provide type safety and help catch errors at compile time.

3)Why HttpClient instead of fetch?
HttpClient supports interceptors, observables, and automatic JSON parsing.

4)What happens inside ngOnInit?
ngOnInit runs after component initialization and is used to fetch initial data.

5)loadUser(id:number)
  {
    this.userService.getUserById(id).subscribe(user => {
      this.userForm.patchValue(user);
    });
  }
What does patchValue() mean?

patchValue() is a Reactive Forms method used to update form values partially.

6)how to create a routing module file
 ng g module features/user --routing

7)What is a pipe in Angular?
A pipe is used to transform data in the template before displaying it to the user.
Pipe does not change the original data, only the view.

Example (Without Pipe)
{{ user.role }} o/p=> ADMIN
With Pipe
{{ user.role | roleDisplay }}  o/p==> Administrator


8)What is a directive in Angular?

âœ… Simple Interview Answer

A directive is a class that allows us to add behavior or modify the appearance of DOM elements.
Custom directives help reuse DOM-related logic across components.
types
1)Component Directive 2)Structural Directive 3)Attribute Directive (ngClass, ngStyle)






